---
import DocLayout from '../../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
---
<DocLayout
  title="agentmako docs — MCP setup, concepts, recipes &amp; tool catalog"
  description="Set up agentmako with Claude Code, Codex CLI, Cursor, or Cline. MCP wiring, plugin install, concepts, recipes, and the full typed tool catalog."
  canonicalPath="/docs/"
  ogImage="/assets/og.png"
  ogImageAlt="agentmako documentation — MCP setup for Claude Code, Codex CLI, Cursor, and Cline."
  ogType="website"
  breadcrumbs={[{"name": "Home", "href": "/"}, {"name": "Docs", "href": "/docs/"}]}
>

<header class="doc-page-header doc-hub__hero">
  <span class="eyebrow">Documentation</span>
  <h1 style="margin-top:1rem;">Wire <em>Mako</em> into your agent.</h1>
  <p class="doc-hero__sub">
    <strong>agentmako</strong> is a local-first MCP server for AI coding
    agents — Claude Code, Codex CLI, Cursor, Cline. Each setup guide is a
    five-minute walk: install, attach a project, paste an MCP config,
    restart the agent, run your first <code>context_packet</code>.
  </p>

  <div class="doc-hub__shortcuts">
    <a class="doc-hub__chip" href="#quickstart">
      <span class="doc-hub__chip-num">01</span>
      <span class="doc-hub__chip-text">
        <strong>Install in 60 seconds</strong>
        <em>npm i -g agentmako, attach, doctor.</em>
      </span>
    </a>
    <a class="doc-hub__chip" href="#setup">
      <span class="doc-hub__chip-num">02</span>
      <span class="doc-hub__chip-text">
        <strong>Wire your agent</strong>
        <em>Claude Code · Codex · Cursor · Cline.</em>
      </span>
    </a>
    <a class="doc-hub__chip" href="./concepts/mcp.html">
      <span class="doc-hub__chip-num">?</span>
      <span class="doc-hub__chip-text">
        <strong>New to MCP?</strong>
        <em>Start with the protocol, then come back.</em>
      </span>
    </a>
  </div>
</header>

<section id="quickstart" class="doc-hub__section">
  <header class="doc-hub__section-head">
    <span class="doc-hub__section-marker">01</span>
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Quickstart</span>
      <h2>A two-step prerequisite, then any agent.</h2>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block__head">
      <span class="code-block__lang">// install &amp; attach a real project</span>
      <button class="copy-inline" data-copy-target="prereq-cmd">Copy</button>
    </div>
<pre id="prereq-cmd"><span class="c-prompt">$</span> npm install -g agentmako
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> cd /path/to/your/project
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> agentmako connect . --no-db
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> agentmako doctor          <span class="c-comment"># expect green</span>
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> agentmako tool list       <span class="c-comment"># confirm tools are registered</span></pre>
  </div>

  <p class="doc-hub__hint">
    Use <code>--no-db</code> for the first run. You can add Postgres /
    Supabase awareness later with interactive
    <code>agentmako connect .</code> or
    <code>--db-env DATABASE_URL --yes</code> for CI.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="setup" class="doc-hub__section">
  <header class="doc-hub__section-head">
    <span class="doc-hub__section-marker">02</span>
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Pick your agent</span>
      <h2>Four harnesses. Same MCP server.</h2>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="agents">
    <a class="agent-card" href="./claude-code.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <img class="agent-card__logo" src="/assets/ai-providers/claudecode-color.svg" alt="" width="32" height="32" loading="lazy" />
          <span class="agent-card__name">Claude Code</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta">
        <span>MCP</span><span>Plugin</span><span>Skills</span>
      </div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Plain MCP wiring, or the bundled <code>mako-ai</code> plugin with
        discovery / trace / graph / database skills.
      </p>
    </a>

    <a class="agent-card" href="./codex.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <img class="agent-card__logo" src="/assets/ai-providers/openai.svg" alt="" width="32" height="32" loading="lazy" />
          <span class="agent-card__name">Codex CLI</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta">
        <span>MCP</span><span>TOML</span>
      </div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Drop into <code>~/.codex/config.toml</code>. Codex picks Mako tools
        up on next run. Works with <code>codex exec</code> and the TUI.
      </p>
    </a>

    <a class="agent-card" href="./cursor.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <img class="agent-card__logo" src="/assets/ai-providers/cursor.svg" alt="" width="32" height="32" loading="lazy" />
          <span class="agent-card__name">Cursor</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta">
        <span>MCP</span><span>Project-scoped</span>
      </div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Per-project <code>.cursor/mcp.json</code> or global config. Composer
        and Agent mode both see Mako tools.
      </p>
    </a>

    <a class="agent-card" href="./cline.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__logo agent-card__logo--text" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"/>
              <polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span class="agent-card__name">Cline</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta">
        <span>MCP</span><span>VS Code</span>
      </div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        VS Code extension. Settings → MCP Servers, paste the snippet,
        reload. Works inside any workspace you've attached.
      </p>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="doc-hub__section">
  <header class="doc-hub__section-head">
    <span class="doc-hub__section-marker">03</span>
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">First commands to try</span>
      <h2>Once it's wired, start with these.</h2>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="feature-grid">
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature__num">i</div>
      <div class="feature__title">tool_search</div>
      <p class="feature__body">
        When you don't yet know which Mako tool fits the job. Returns the
        right tool plus a reason.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature__num">ii</div>
      <div class="feature__title">context_packet</div>
      <p class="feature__body">
        When you have a coding task. Returns the file, routes, symbols,
        findings, and what to read next.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature__num">iii</div>
      <div class="feature__title">reef_scout</div>
      <p class="feature__body">
        When you want ranked candidates for a fuzzy question. Facts,
        findings, and prior reviews — all weighted.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Tip</strong>
    <p>Copy the agent guidance from
    <a href="https://github.com/drhalto/agentmako/blob/main/AGENTS.md">AGENTS.md</a>
    into your project's <code>CLAUDE.md</code> / <code>AGENTS.md</code>. It
    tells the agent <em>when</em> to call which Mako tool — without it
    they default to grep.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="doc-hub__section">
  <header class="doc-hub__section-head">
    <span class="doc-hub__section-marker">04</span>
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Concepts</span>
      <h2>How agentmako thinks about a codebase.</h2>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="agents">
    <a class="agent-card" href="./concepts/mcp.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">What is MCP?</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Concept</span><span>Standard</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        The Model Context Protocol — what it is, where it came from,
        why one server runs against every coding agent.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./concepts/context-packets.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Context packets</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Concept</span><span>Determinism</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        What <code>context_packet</code> returns: ranked files, related
        routes, active findings, and a "read next" pointer.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./concepts/reef-engine.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Reef Engine</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Concept</span><span>Memory</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Durable facts and findings that persist across agent sessions —
        so the next turn does not re-discover everything.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./concepts/freshness.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Freshness model</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Concept</span><span>Trust</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        How Mako labels evidence as live, fresh_indexed, stale,
        contradicted, or unknown — and why "stable" is not "fresh."
      </p>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="doc-hub__section">
  <header class="doc-hub__section-head">
    <span class="doc-hub__section-marker">05</span>
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Recipes</span>
      <h2>Walk-throughs for the common agent tasks.</h2>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="agents">
    <a class="agent-card" href="./recipes/auth-flow-tracing.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Trace an auth flow</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Recipe</span><span>auth_path</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Bug report says "manager role check is failing." Walk a route
        to its handler, find the RLS, fix the bug.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./recipes/safe-refactoring.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Refactor safely</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Recipe</span><span>imports_impact</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Renaming an exported function across a real codebase without
        shipping broken callers.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./recipes/database-aware-edits.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Schema-aware edits</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Recipe</span><span>db_table_schema</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Add a Postgres column with RLS, find every code site that
        touches the table, audit tenant isolation.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./recipes/debugging-with-context.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Debug with context</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Recipe</span><span>context_packet</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        A real "hydration error" debug session — start from
        <code>context_packet</code>, narrow with freshness, fix.
      </p>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="doc-hub__section">
  <header class="doc-hub__section-head">
    <span class="doc-hub__section-marker">06</span>
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Reference</span>
      <h2>Tools, CLI, dashboard, FAQ.</h2>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="agents">
    <a class="agent-card" href="./tools/">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Tool catalog</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Reference</span><span>85 tools</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Every typed MCP tool, by category. Read or mutation, with input
        and output examples.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./cli.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">CLI reference</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Reference</span><span>commands</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Every <code>agentmako</code> command — connect, doctor, mcp,
        project, providers, and the optional harness suite.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./dashboard.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Dashboard</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Reference</span><span>local web UI</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        Optional Vite + React dashboard. Browse projects, run tools,
        inspect Reef state, chat with the harness — local-only.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./faq.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">FAQ</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Reference</span><span>30+ Qs</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        MCP fundamentals, codebase context, agentmako specifics, and
        troubleshooting.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a class="agent-card" href="./troubleshooting.html">
      <div class="agent-card__head">
        <div class="agent-card__title">
          <span class="agent-card__name">Troubleshooting</span>
        </div>
        <span class="agent-card__arrow">↗</span>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-card__meta"><span>Reference</span><span>Diagnosis</span></div>
      <p class="agent-card__desc">
        "MCP server fails to start", "tools don't appear", "stale
        results" — diagnose and fix in one place.
      </p>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="doc-hub__outro">
  <div class="doc-hub__outro-card">
    <span class="eyebrow">What's next</span>
    <h2>Read the thinking, watch the traffic.</h2>
    <p>
      The blog covers the cost story, what grep can't do for an agent,
      multi-tenant audit patterns, and cross-session memory with
      Reef. Practical posts; no hype.
    </p>
    <div class="doc-hub__outro-actions">
      <a class="am-btn am-btn-ghost am-btn-sm" href="/blog/">Read the blog &rarr;</a>
      <a class="am-btn am-btn-ghost am-btn-sm" href="https://github.com/drhalto/agentmako" rel="noopener">Star on GitHub</a>
      <a class="am-btn am-btn-ghost am-btn-sm" href="/CLAUDE.md" download>Download CLAUDE.md</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</DocLayout>
